data/onto-obo/alignment-kernel-v0.json:2:  "purpose": "Hand-checked candidate bridges from the hand-authored kernel-v0 (54 Explicated profile-1 concepts) and molecules-v0 (54 molecules) into the onto-obo bulk tier (BFO/RO/GO). These are ANNOTATION-layer bridge candidates (categorial correspondences), NOT identity claims. BFO/RO are a foundational realist ontology and gUFO (which kernel-v0 already targets: gufo:Event, gufo:Kind) is a BFO-adjacent lightweight UFO; kernel-v0 concepts are NSM explications. The correspondence is 'this NSM concept falls under this BFO category / uses this RO relation', not sameConceptAs. Nothing here is endorsed and nothing enters the mapper.",
data/onto-obo/alignment-kernel-v0.json:3:  "method": "manual review by the extracting agent (2026-07-07) against the pinned onto-obo records. Only correspondences the agent is confident of are listed; confidence + caveat per link. gUFO is the intended bridge target for the Event/Kind alignments (kernel-v0 uses gufo: URIs); BFO is cited because gUFO's categories are BFO-aligned and BFO is what we extracted.",
data/onto-obo/alignment-kernel-v0.json:17:      "note": "kernel-v0:event (gufo:Event: 'this something happens at some time; after this time it is not happening') is a BFO occurrent, specifically a process. The directive's named anchor (BFO continuant/occurrent <-> our Event). Also fallsUnder BFO:0000003 (occurrent)."
data/onto-obo/alignment-kernel-v0.json:25:      "note": "The genus one level up from process; gufo:Event corresponds to BFO occurrent (something with temporal parts that unfolds in time)."
data/onto-obo/alignment-kernel-v0.json:57:      "note": "kernel-v0:kind (gufo:Kind: a rigid sortal, 'it cannot not be of this kind') is a META-type of continuants (a kind classifies endurants), not a BFO class itself; BFO has no rigidity meta-level. Low-confidence categorial hint only."
